g.text: RX side of PMD will pass the address (or offset) of the mbuf header to the Fill Queue•This address is the start of the buffer being usedRX packet data is places at the following address•addr = (char *)mbuf + sizeof(pktmbuf_t);•addr += XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM;•addr += xdp_umem.head_room; // (normally zero)RX Ring returns packet offset address•Need to subtract off the XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM to get access to mbuf
Packet data starts at 256 bytes offset from buffer XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM
